1. Prepare ``test.data'' file for target layout of 3-D chip stacking

File format (each line):
chipname, Z-axis(1,2,...), X-axis, Y-axis, Frequency(MHz), chip rotation(not supported yet)
TULSA 1 0.00 0.00 1380 0  
TULSA 1 0.03 0.00 541 0
TULSA 1 0.00 0.03 3400 0
TULSA 1 0.03 0.03 185 0
TULSA 2 0.04 0.04 541 0 
TULSA 2 0.01 0.01 3400 0

# Currently, Only Intel Tulsa processor chip is supported.
# Intel Tulsa chip:0.02184 x 0.02184 (m).

2. Execution for test.data
make
python hotspot.py [water | air | oil ]

results
./tmp.results -> a highest temperature of modules on all chips
./figure/*.pdf -> Temperature distribution of all chips.

# Notice that temperature_grid.c is updated on HotSpot-6.0 distribution.

